Fit Mixed Effects Model for Mystery Caller Study with Logging

Source: R/results_section_fit_mixed_model_with_logging.R
results_section_fit_mixed_model_with_logging.Rd

This function fits a mixed-effects model to analyze the association between appointment wait times and insurance type, with random effects for state or physician ID. It logs the model creation and diagnostics at each step.

Usage

results_section_fit_mixed_model_with_logging(
  wait_time_data,
  outcome_var,
  random_effects,
  fixed_effects,
  verbose = FALSE
)

Arguments

wait_time_data

A data frame with columns including wait_time, insurance_type, state, physician_id, and other demographic factors.

outcome_var

A string specifying the outcome variable, typically wait_time.

random_effects

A character vector of variables to include as random effects (e.g., state, physician_id).

fixed_effects

A character vector of fixed effect variables to include in the model (e.g., insurance_type, scenario).

verbose

Logical. If TRUE, prints detailed model diagnostics.

Value

A list containing the fitted mixed-effects model and summaries.
